The paper deals with lower bounds and algorithms for Boolean functions computable by de Morgan formulas, which is a topic in computational complexity theory (cs.CC). The use of classes of functions with low communication complexity suggests a connection to information theory (cs.IT) and communication complexity (cs.CC). The paper also mentions the use of probabilistically checkable proofs (cs.DS) and learning algorithms (cs.LG). Finally, the paper deals with the Minimum Circuit Size Problem, which is a topic in discrete mathematics (cs.DM).
